# Layer 7 - Application

## Overview

This task introduced the Application Layer, which is Layer 7 and the highest layer of the OSI Model. The Application Layer is the closest layer to the end user and provides the protocols, services, and interfaces that allow users to interact with networked applications and data.

---

## Objectives

* Understand the purpose of the Application Layer.
* Learn how users interact with network services.
* Identify common applications that operate at this layer.
* Understand the role of application protocols.
* Learn how DNS supports network communication.

