## Key Findings / Notes

* The Application Layer is Layer 7 of the OSI Model.
* It is the highest layer in the OSI framework.
* Users interact directly with this layer.
* Provides access to network services and resources.
* Supports applications such as browsers and email clients.
* Uses application-level protocols to facilitate communication.
* DNS translates domain names into IP addresses.
* GUIs make network services accessible to end users.

